# 6. Feature Requirements

## Feature 1 — Sign Up

Requirements:

- Name
- Email
- Password
- Form validation
- Password strength indicator
- Password hashing
- Verification email

Acceptance Criteria:

- Invalid input rejected
- Password hashed
- User created
- Verification token generated
- Email sent

---

## Feature 2 — Login

Requirements:

- Credentials login
- NextAuth session
- Secure error handling

Acceptance Criteria:

- Valid login succeeds
- Invalid login rejected
- Session created
- No leaked information

---

## Feature 3 — Email Verification

Requirements:

- Secure token generation
- Database token storage
- Expiry handling
- Verification endpoint

Acceptance Criteria:

- Token validated
- Expired token rejected
- User verified
- Token deleted

---

## Feature 4 — Forgot Password

Requirements:

- Email request
- Token creation
- Reset email
- New password flow

Acceptance Criteria:

- Token expires
- Password rehashed
- Token deleted
- Redirect works

---

## Feature 5 — Protected Dashboard

Requirements:

- Middleware protection
- Session validation
- Verification check

Acceptance Criteria:

- Verified users allowed
- Others redirected

---

## Feature 6 — Logout

Requirements:

- Session destruction
- Redirect

Acceptance Criteria:

- Session removed
- Redirect login

---

## Feature 7 — Security Hardening

Requirements:

- Rate limiting
- Security headers
- Sanitized errors
- Environment protection

Acceptance Criteria:

- Login brute force blocked
- Secrets hidden
- Headers active

---

# 7. Non-Goals (YAGNI Scope Control)

The following are intentionally excluded:

- Social login
- Multi-factor authentication
- Admin dashboard
- User roles
- Payments
- Audit logs
- OAuth providers
- Analytics

These features are valuable but outside current MVP scope.

---

# 8. Security Requirements

SecureGate follows security-first engineering.

Mandatory requirements:

- bcrypt hashing
- Salt rounds = 12
- Token expiry
- No plaintext passwords
- No hardcoded secrets
- Rate limiting
- Generic auth errors
- Server-side validation
- Protected routes

